Repro program (assuming a bucket named "sean-testbucket" exists):

```javascript
"use strict";
const pulumi = require("@pulumi/pulumi");
const aws = require("@pulumi/aws");

const bucket = aws.s3.Bucket.get("bucket", "sean-testbucket");
const obj = new aws.s3.BucketObject("testobj", {
    bucket: bucket.id,
    content: "text"
});

exports.bucketName = bucket.bucketDomainName;
```

`pulumi update` fails with

```
error: failed to load language plugin nodejs: failed to perform plugin load callback: failed to save snapshot: after mutation of snapshot: resource urn:pulumi:get-dev::get::aws:s3/bucketObject:BucketObject::testobj dependency urn:pulumi:get-dev::get::pulumi:pulumi:Stack$aws:s3/bucket:Bucket::bucket refers to missing resource
```

The problem is that we do not place resources obtained from `Resource.get` in the snapshot. This is a problem for us. Depending on an Output property of a `Resource.get` resource causes us to record the dependency in the snapshot, but since we don't put `Resource.get` resources in the snapshot, snapshot verification fails.

